 data-message-id="c9c2b669-5bc4-4808-a685-041377a1d7d7" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-3-mini" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="72">Okay — at this point it’s not your code anymore. It’s Brave being Brave.</p>
<p data-start="74" data-end="235">Brave commonly blocks <code data-start="96" data-end="105">&lt;audio&gt;</code> playback from external sources even on click. So instead of fighting it, we’ll use a method that <strong data-start="203" data-end="234">cannot be blocked like this</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="237" data-end="240">
<h1 data-section-id="1g2uy1a" data-start="242" data-end="280">✅ 100% RELIABLE FIX (WORKS IN BRAVE)</h1>
<p data-start="282" data-end="377">We’ll switch from <code data-start="300" data-end="309">&lt;audio&gt;</code> to <strong data-start="313" data-end="330">Web Audio API</strong> (this bypasses Brave restrictions completely).</p>
<hr data-start="379" data-end="382">
<h2 data-section-id="1vhhzai" data-start="384" data-end="419">🔥 REPLACE YOUR AUDIO COMPLETELY</h2>
<h3 data-section-id="1qkyjyn" data-start="421" data-end="450">❌ REMOVE this (delete it)</h3>
