end="119">Got it — GitHub Pages changes the setup a bit, so the “just put it in a folder” advice needs to be translated properly.</p>
<p data-start="121" data-end="168">Let’s make this <strong data-start="137" data-end="167">simple and GitHub-friendly</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="170" data-end="173">
<h1 data-section-id="1ff7gxr" data-start="175" data-end="217">🚫 Why your audio is confusing right now</h1>
<p data-start="219" data-end="235">In GitHub Pages:</p>
<ul data-start="236" data-end="415">
<li data-section-id="8nb97a" data-start="236" data-end="279">
<p data-start="238" data-end="279">You don’t “run files locally in a folder”</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="fhuv0j" data-start="280" data-end="316">
<p data-start="282" data-end="316">You are serving a <strong data-start="300" data-end="316">live website</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1tio2w4" data-start="317" data-end="369">
<p data-start="319" data-end="369">External audio links can still be blocked by Brave</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="19po0r8" data-start="370" data-end="415">
<p data-start="372" data-end="415">And Web Audio oscillator ≠ real paper sound</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="417" data-end="456">So we need a <strong data-start="430" data-end="456">GitHub-native solution</strong></p>
<hr data-start="458" data-end="461">
<h1 data-section-id="suazsg" data-start="463" data-end="506">✅ BEST SETUP FOR GITHUB PAGES (NO ISSUES)</h1>
<h2 data-section-id="6zzin8" data-start="508" data-end="564">🟢 OPTION 1 (RECOMMENDED): Put audio inside your repo</h2>
<p data-start="566" data-end="643">Even if you don’t think of it as a “folder”, GitHub <em data-start="618" data-end="622">is</em> structured like one.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="hwehlx" data-start="645" data-end="660">👉 Do this:</h3>
<p data-start="662" data-end="694">In your GitHub repo, add a file:</p>
