<hr data-start="936" data-end="939">
<h1 data-section-id="wh8k48" data-start="941" data-end="988">⚠️ IMPORTANT (why your previous links failed)</h1>
<p data-start="990" data-end="1010">External links like:</p>
<ul data-start="1011" data-end="1040">
<li data-section-id="15d9sma" data-start="1011" data-end="1019">
<p data-start="1013" data-end="1019">mixkit</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="orxjua" data-start="1020" data-end="1029">
<p data-start="1022" data-end="1029">pixabay</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="ue8509" data-start="1030" data-end="1040">
<p data-start="1032" data-end="1040">soundjay</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1042" data-end="1119">❌ are not reliable inside Brave<br data-start="1073" data-end="1076">
❌ sometimes blocked as cross-origin media</p>
<p data-start="1121" data-end="1199">But GitHub Pages:<br>
✔ is same-origin<br data-start="1155" data-end="1158">
✔ fully trusted<br data-start="1173" data-end="1176">
✔ stable for projects</p>
<hr data-start="1201" data-end="1204">
<h1 data-section-id="nln60y" data-start="1206" data-end="1230">💡 SIMPLE RULE FOR YOU</h1>
<p data-start="1232" data-end="1328">👉 If file = in GitHub repo → use GitHub Pages link<br data-start="1283" data-end="1286">
👉 If file = external → Brave may block it</p>
